 Pollonia, Milos.<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-12-visit-trypiti-village\">12. Visit Trypiti village<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This charming hilltop village spreads slowly down the hill, and visiting is a thing you must do in Milos. Within the village, you&#x2019;ll find traditional windmills, beautiful churches, and a maze of streets to get lost in. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1.jpg\" alt=\"milos island greece\"><\/noscript><img width=\"262\" height=\"338\" alt=\"milos island greece\" class=\"wp-image-60200 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1489px) 100vw, 1489px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1.jpg 1489w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-465x600.jpg 465w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-628x810.jpg 628w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-262x338.jpg 262w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-23x30.jpg 23w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-126x163.jpg 126w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-140x180.jpg 140w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-596x768.jpg 596w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-794x1024.jpg 794w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-838x1080.jpg 838w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-1117x1440.jpg 1117w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-300x387.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-600x774.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1-23x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/14112218\/milos-greece-Trypiti-village1.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Trypa is the Greek word for &#x2018;hole&#x2019;, and the village is named this way because of the holes in the rocks surrounding the town. These holes were used as storage by the local people and burial chambers like the Catacombs of Milos. The Catacombs and the Theater are just down the hill from the village.&#xA0;<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>You can walk to Trypiti along the hiking trail from Plaka (roughly a 20-minute walk). We advise doing island hikes during the spring or autumn months when there are cooler temperatures and a lovely Greek island breeze!&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><